Mexican President Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador shows an alleged spy camera found by the cleaning staff in the National Palace, during his daily morning press conference in Mexico City on Tuesday. "We were being recorded," Lopez Obrador said. He did not indicate who could be behind the alleged espionage, but said he was not worried because he has nothing to hide.   
